[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_g1kfd")
release_version = "v1.2.2"
notes = "[TITLE]Items
Slightly tweaked the Special Items treasure pool
Toon-Up items will now stack the rounds the effect will last, rather than the potency of the effect
In the wake of these changes to Toon-Up, the following balance changes have been made:
  All Toon-Up items last 1 fewer round
  The maximum Toon-Up item count has been increased to 5
  Toon-Up items have been made slightly more rare overall
  Feather now boosts Defense by 50% (previously 30%)
  Bamboo Cane now boosts Evasiveness by 50% (previously 40%)
  Megaphone now boosts Damage by 20% (previously 10%)
  Juggling Cubes now boosts Luck by 25% (previously 20%)
  Lipstick's gag discount has been increased to 2
  High Dive's boosts have also been increased:
    +15% Damage (previously 10%)
    +20% Luck (previously 15%)
    +35% Defense (previously 20%)
    +35% Evasiveness (previously 25%)
  Combining a High Dive stat boost with another Toon-Up stat boost will increase the rounds of the stat boost, and take the higher of the two boost amounts
Laff Boosts at the shop will now scale in price with their boost amount
[TITLE]Bosses
The following changes were made to The Directors:
  Increased the HP of each Director to 3000
  Increased the level range of grunt Cogs during the fight
  The first reinforcement call will now occur at the end of the first round
[TITLE]Tweaks
Group Lure's Accuracy Down is now properly reflected in the GUI and during the battle movie
Lightened the floor in the Cog Golf Course mazes
All ToonTask slots can now roll a task related to any department
[TITLE]Bugfixes
Fixed an issue where Bird Wings could cause shopkeepers' accessories to glow
Fixed a bug where Heart Glasses could cause Embezzle to steal negative quantities of jellybeans
Fixed a bug that would cause items to be unable to be picked up when rerolled with Paint Bucket
Fixed an issue that allowed you to use Toy Hammer and Big Foghorn on the Chartist boss fight
Fixed an issue where White-Out could spawn you partway through a floor
Fixed a crash in the shop related to swapping Pocket Pranks
Fixed an issue where the Toxic Proxy Cog effect wouldn't scale its effects properly
Similarly, fixed an issue where Toxic wouldn't properly apply Budget Cuts to Professor Pete
Fixed a bug in the Cog Creator where the proxy status effect wouldn't be properly added to the Cog's DNA file
Fixed some wonky battle collisions
The connectors in the Cog Golf Course no longer consume the chests in the maze room
Fixed the respawn point of a lava floor in the Molten Mint
Adjusted an invisible wall in the Molten Mint"
